,'inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-21 18:10:14','2015-10-21 18:10:14','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/21/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2015-10-21 20:43:53','2015-10-21 20:43:53','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians via campaign contributions. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this kind of adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the\r\nenvironment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-21 20:43:53','2015-10-21 20:43:53','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/21/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(35,1,'2015-10-21 20:46:47','2015-10-21 20:46:47','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21, 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians via campaign contributions. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this kind of adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the\r\nenvironment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-21 20:46:47','2015-10-21 20:46:47','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/21/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2015-10-21 22:32:56','2015-10-21 22:32:56','','IMG_0373','','inherit','open','closed','','img_0373','','','2015-10-21 22:33:51','2015-10-21 22:33:51','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IMG_03731.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(37,1,'2015-10-21 22:42:35','2015-10-21 22:42:35','','photo(4)','some corn somewhere ','inherit','open','closed','','photo4','','','2015-10-21 22:52:53','2015-10-21 22:52:53','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(38,1,'2015-10-21 23:06:40','2015-10-21 23:06:40','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_37\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"857\"]<a href=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\" alt=\"some corn somewhere \" width=\"857\" height=\"515\" class=\"size-full wp-image-37\" /></a> some corn somewhere [/caption]\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21, 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians via campaign contributions. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this kind of adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the\r\nenvironment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-21 23:06:40','2015-10-21 23:06:40','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/21/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(39,1,'2015-10-22 07:19:15','2015-10-22 07:19:15','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_37\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"857\"]<a href=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\" alt=\"some corn somewhere \" width=\"857\" height=\"515\" class=\"size-full wp-image-37\" /></a> some corn somewhere [/caption]\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21, 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians via campaign contributions. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this kind of adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the environment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-22 07:19:15','2015-10-22 07:19:15','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/22/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2015-10-22 07:38:54','2015-10-22 07:38:54','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_37\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"857\"]<a href=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\" alt=\"some corn somewhere \" width=\"857\" height=\"515\" class=\"size-full wp-image-37\" /></a> some corn somewhere [/caption]\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21, 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians via campaign contributions. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the environment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-22 07:38:54','2015-10-22 07:38:54','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/22/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(41,1,'2015-10-22 07:45:33','2015-10-22 07:45:33','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'</font>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_37\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"857\"]<a href=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/photo4.jpg\" alt=\"some corn somewhere \" width=\"857\" height=\"515\" class=\"size-full wp-image-37\" /></a> some corn somewhere [/caption]\r\nby <a href=\"https://twitter.com/skennycomedy\">Sarah Kenny</a> October 21, 2015\r\n\r\nST. LOUIS – Polls show that over 90% of US consumers think that foods containing genetically\r\nmodified organisms (GMOs) should be labeled as such. Monsanto is one of the largest producers of\r\nGM seeds, in a recent interview their CEO, Hugh Grant, explains why his company is doing\r\neverything in its power to fight mandatory GMO labeling laws.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> So, what are some of the issues associated with labeling GM foods?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat; no doubt about that and this effort to label them is anti-science & anti-\r\ntechnology. The reason consumers want to label or ban GMOs is purely out of a fear of technology. We know for a fact that people are afraid of technology, that\'s exactly why smartphones haven\'t really caught on, especially in developing countries. Their manufacturers made the mistake of not investing in outreach & education to convince consumers it was a worthwhile product, like we do with GMOs.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> How much of your budget would you say goes towards public relations & outreach to try and gain consumer acceptance of your technology?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Funny you should ask. We recently made a brilliant discovery that buying scientists (even from Harvard) for promotional purposes is nearly 800% cheaper than buying politicians. Because of this we\'ve managed to reduce our PR spending to a mere 75% of our annual budget.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many scientists worry about the increased use of pesticides associated with GMO cultivation & its effects on biodiversity; do you think this is influencing the demand for labeling?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just because your food came from a toxic wasteland uninhabitable by anything not engineered to withstand poison does not mean that that food is unsafe so why should we label it? And these fears about bees, butterflies, worms and whatnot dying off are totally unfounded when you consider the vast resources of a company like Monsanto. We are confident that we can re-engineer every species on the planet to survive in this post-apocalyptic type of environment, and this adaptive capability is something that I\'m extremely proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wow. So, if GMOs are so great then why are they banned in so many countries & why does their introduction cause civil unrest in so many others?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Sarah, GMOs are perfectly safe to eat. The banning of GMO cultivation in Scotland, Ireland, Italy, Germany, Austria, Greece, Latvia, Serbia, Russia, France & elsewhere and the protests you hear about in Mexico, Kenya, Argentina, Brazil, Nigeria, etc. are all just classic cases of misunderstanding caused mainly by fascist food bloggers.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Is it possible all these people simply don\'t like your products?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> No\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What are the possible risks & downsides associated with GMOs?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Thousands of studies have found zero possible negative effects from our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> That sounds statistically impossible\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not, we used science.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Your website claims that GMOs help reduce pesticide usage, so why are you trying to buy\r\nSyngenta, the largest pesticide producer in the world?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Just in case\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> What about cross-pollination? How can an organic farmer protect his crops from contamination\r\nfrom a neighboring GM field?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> GMOs are safe to eat\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Many GMO farmers grow just a few types of plants. Doesn\'t this “mono-cropping” make our food system vulnerable?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Right, but the thing is GMOs are safe to eat.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Do you think if GM foods were labeled in the US your company would lose money?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> It\'s not about profits necessarily; our opposition to labeling of GMOs is common sense really. I mean, haven\'t you ever been so proud of something you created that you would go to absolutely any\r\nlengths to conceal it?\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> umm...\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> That\'s why I\'m using all the financial and political resources of the greatest biotechnology company on Earth to fight the misinformation & to change the minds of the misguided people who judge our products with skepticism just because we poisoned a few million people in the past.\r\n\r\n<strong>SK:</strong> Wait, what?\r\n\r\n<strong>HG:</strong> Our products are so safe & so healthy for people and the environment that I will label them over my dead body.\r\n','Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled over my dead body\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2015-10-22 07:45:33','2015-10-22 07:45:33','',2,'http://ec2-54-68-184-179.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com/index.php/2015/10/22/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(42,1,'2015-10-22 07:50:41','2015-10-22 07:50:41','<font size=\"8\">Monsanto CEO: \'GMOs will be labeled 